Introduced Version
HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. ___
Introduced by: Pryor, Harris, Jackson C, Bartlett, Burton,
Hatcher, Pack, Porter, Shackleford, Smith V, Summers
____________________________________
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION recognizing May 2026 as
2 Lupus Awareness Month.
3 Whereas, Lupus is a chronic autoimmune disease affecting
4 an estimated 1.5 million Americans with a disproportionately
5 negative impact on women and especially African American,
6 Hispanic/Latina, Asian American, Native American, Alaska
7 Native, Native Hawaiian, and other Pacific Islander women;
8 Whereas, Lupus causes the immune system to attack healthy
9 tissue, resulting in widespread systemic inflammation and
10 damage to organs such as the skin, joints, kidneys, heart, lungs,
11 and brain;
12 Whereas, Symptoms of lupus can be highly variable,
13 affecting the musculoskeletal, nervous, blood, immune, and
20262400
HR 1536/DI 140 2026

2
1 reproductive systems, and it can also cause increased risks of
2 cancer, chronic pain, fatigue, hair loss, eye complications, and
3 psychological effects, making diagnosis and treatment of the
4 disease difficult;
5 Whereas, The variability of this condition often leads to
6 delays in treatment, increased health care costs, and reduced
7 quality of life for patients;
8 Whereas, Public education campaigns, clinical trials, and
9 affordable health care are needed to improve early diagnosis,
10 reduce treatment time lags, and enhance lupus education
11 among both health care providers and the general public, as
12 there is no known cure for lupus;
13 Whereas, May is recognized nationwide as Lupus Awareness
14 Month, a time to educate the public, advocate for additional
15 research funding, and acknowledge the strength of those
16 struggling with this chronic disease;
17 Whereas, President Ronald Reagan first designated a
18 national month of awareness "to mark our great concern for
19 the thousands of Americans who suffer from lupus." Other
20 leaders have also joined this important cause; and
21 Whereas, Indiana must join these efforts to raise awareness,
22 reduce health disparities, and support individuals and families
23 affected by lupus: Therefore,
24 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
25 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
26 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
27 recognizes May 2026 as Lupus Awareness Month to raise
28 awareness of this debilitating autoimmune disease and its
29 impact on communities throughout Indiana.
30 SECTION 2. That the Indiana House of Representatives
31 recognizes the need for expanded research funding, public
32 education campaigns, and efforts to make treatments more
33 accessible to those affected by lupus.
34 SECTION 3. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
35 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to State
